Title: The 'eu' in eucatastrophe – Why SciPy builds for Python 3.12 on Windows are a minor miracle
Description: Moving SciPy to Meson meant finding a different Fortran compiler on Windows, which was particularly tricky to pull off for conda-forge. This blog tells the story about how things looked pretty grim for the Python 3.12 release, and how things ended up working out just in the nick of time.
